On August 27th I placed a delivery order, and everything went well. The pizza and wings were good, the soda was cold, and they even gave me extra cups and plates.  But then things got weird...  Last weekend, and today I've received calls from Pizza Hut delivery drivers letting me know they were on their way to my hotel (I stayed at the Hilton Atlanta for Dragon Con).  I called at 7PM, and spoke with the manager (Eric). He seemed perplexed by what was going on, and called the driver to cancel the delivery. He also mentioned refunding my credit card.  He stated another Pizza Hut must have placed the order, but I verified the number before calling and asking to speak with a manager. This was the only Pizza Hut I called in Atlanta.  I'm now working through all of my credit cards to find fraudulent charges for pizza because it was late when I placed the order on the 27th and I don't remember which card I used. This whole thing is surreal and leads to a slew of questions. - who's placing the order - how do they have my cell #, and hotel delivery information - how many other people is this happening to  Depending on what I find will determine who contacts Pizza Hut corporate (me, or my atrorneys).  It may be a glitch, or it may be more nefarious. But I urge everyone to reconsider using a credit card.
